The correct answer is B. Single-pass in memory indexing algorithm.  

For a moderately large, static collection on a single system, this algorithm is efficient because it processes documents in one pass and builds the index entirely in memory without needing distributed or dynamic structures. Block sort-based indexing (A) is more suited for very large collections, while distributed (C) and dynamic (D) approaches add unnecessary complexity for a static, single-system scenario.  

\boxed{B}
